Toyah Ann Willcox (born 18 May 1958) is an English singer and actress.
In a career spanning more than thirty years, Willcox has had 8 Top 40
singles, released over 20 albums, written two books, appeared in over
forty stage plays and ten feature films, and voiced and presented
numerous television shows.[1] Between 1977 and 1983 she fronted the
band Toyah, before embarking on a solo career in the mid-1980s. Her
biggest hits include "It's a Mystery", "Thunder in the Mountains"
and "I Want to Be Free".
